    <main>
      <h2>Lake Preston in the wet</h2>
      
      <div class="content">
	<p>
	  Rolling sprays in sandy groves<br>
	  Dampen my denim jacket<br>
	  Wit a crust of salt, the sheets of waves<br>
	  Surging for pole position
	</p>

	<p>
	  Up the limestone moonscape road<br>
	  My pale skin satched to the bone<br>
	  Porcelain shells cracking<br>
	  Under foot, the wind howling
	</p>

	<p>
	  In silence for generations into the mists<br>
	  Still rolling torrents screaming<br>
	  With the tweets of finches<br>
	  The frost in my fingers
	</p>

	<p>
	  In the fluorescent underscrub<br>
	  Flowered and verdanted<br>
	  Jagged leaf blades and soft<br>
	  Little petals, purple spotted
	</p>

	<p>
	  Vulvas sitting ripe in the rain,<br>
	  Drops of water beading down<br>
	  Sweetly, the treacled blood<br>
	  Still flowing through my veins
	</p>

	<p>
	  Shivering in the cold wet mud<br>
	  In my socks, a besotted kangaroo<br>
	  Smashing through the undergrowth<br>
	  In my sights, against the backdrop
	</p>

	<p>
	  Of the highway, the wind sings<br>
	  And the rain dances in this<br>
	  My personal theatre, this<br>
	  Magnificent place
	</p>
      </div>
      
